Features  More Info         Common Questions   Common Questions   Who do I contact if I have questions regarding Data Center ?  What are some features and requirements of the ACCC West Campus Data Center ?  What is the cost analysis regarding different Data Center Service offerings ?  More…            Features    Standard 1 GB Ethernet to campus backbone is available  The Data Center is under video surveillance 24/7  All locations are secured 24/7  Access is granted through authorization by contacting ACCC Network Operations Center  Fire suppression and environmental controls  ACCC will ensure the data center operates within the Industry (ASHRAE) recommend cooling range for data centers  ACCC will notify tenant of planned maintenance and incidents that may impact co-located equipment  In case of a planned outage for an infrastructure system (e.g., power outage, UPS testing), each tenant will be contacted in advance  Change controls and planned outages will occur during the standard change control window  Infrastructure components and systems are covered under support and maintenance contracts and tested weekly, monthly, bi-annually, or quarterly, depending on component       Features Across All Tiers        Bronze  Silver  Gold      Temperature and humidity controlled environment  ✓  ✓  ✓    Fire detection and suppression system  ✓  ✓  ✓    Physical security and video monitoring  ✓  ✓  ✓    UPS power conditioning and backup    ✓  ✓    Emergency generator      ✓    Remote support from on-site staff      ✓    Datacenter access and on-site support  By Appointment  5x8  7x24    Network connections included per Rack Unit (1U)  1  2  2    Yearly charge per Rack Unit (1U) - up to 300W  $72.00  $120.00  $216.00              More Info   Requirements   All authorized tenants and visitors must sign in/out at designated sign in sheet  Server must meet rack mount specifications  Contact information for server administrators, departmental personnel, and hardware inventory must be updated / kept current at all times   Applicability  Clients are responsible for adhering to the following Administrative Guidelines while utilizing this service:   Tenant must not interfere with ACCC hardware or property, including moving raised-floor tiles  Tenant is not authorized to use data center space for long-term storage of non-production hardware or accessories (e.g. cardboard boxes)  Tenants are responsible for not overloading their circuits and are required to contact the ACCC Staff prior to executing new equipment installations  Tenants of this service are responsible for the installation, operation, and maintenance of the equipment in their rack(s)  Data Center access on your key card or allowing an escorted guest means you are agreeing to the terms outlined in the Data Center access agreement document               Google Maps image     C-Stop, BSB   1007 West Harrison Street,  Behavioral Sciences Building(BSB), Learning Center, First Floor,  Chicago,  IL    Phone: (312) 413-0003  Website: https://accc.uic.edu/support         Service Level Agreement       Service Request Fulfillment Time  Fulfillment time is dependent on Bronze, Silver, or Gold level of selection    Incident Resolution Time  Incident resolution time is dependent on Bronze, Silver, or Gold level of selection    Service Availability  24x7    Maintenance Window(s)  ​Approved ACCC maintenance window(s)    Service Notification Channel(s)  ACCC Service Notices    Reviewed to Ensure SLA Meets Business Requirements  Provisional SLA - Currently under IT Governance review    Date Reviewed  Provisional SLA - Currently under IT Governance review    Service Owner: Jelene Crehan (Interim)               Services    Back to main content           Communication and Collaboration     Cloud Storage     Box    Google Drive    OneDrive      Conferencing     Blackboard Collaborate    Google Meet    Webex Meetings    Zoom      Digital Signage     Industry Weapon      Email and Calendaring     Exchange    G